11
0:00:35.875,000 --> 0:00:38,000
and I realize that some parts of me have dropped

12
0:00:39.2,000 --> 0:00:41,000
and I can't find them down there.

13
0:00:41.832,000 --> 0:00:42,000
(Laughter)

14
0:00:42.97,000 --> 0:00:45,000
Mary Oliver says in one of her poems,

15
0:00:46.169,000 --> 0:00:49,000
"Tell me, what is it that you plan to do

16
0:00:49.848,000 --> 0:00:52,000
with your one wild and precious life?"

17
0:00:53.531,000 --> 0:00:57,000
Me, I intend to live passionately.

18
0:00:57.834,000 --> 0:00:59,000
When do we start aging?

19
0:00:59.846,000 --> 0:01:01,000
Society decides when we are old,

20
0:01:02.233,000 --> 0:01:06,000
usually around 65, when we get Medicare,

21
0:01:06.464,000 --> 0:01:08,000
but we really start aging at birth.

22
0:01:09.23,000 --> 0:01:1,000
We are aging right now,

23
0:01:11.19,000 --> 0:01:14,000
and we all experience it differently.

24
0:01:14.383,000 --> 0:01:17,000
We all feel younger than our real age,

25
0:01:17.825,000 --> 0:01:19,000
because the spirit never ages.

26
0:01:19.996,000 --> 0:01:22,000
I am still 17.

27
0:01:23.291,000 --> 0:01:26,000
Sophia Loren. Look at her.

28
0:01:26.82,000 --> 0:01:28,000
She says that everything you see

29
